TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—Seasonal Exponential Smoothing with Damped Trends
AU  - Gardner, Everette S.
AU  - McKenzie, Ed.
Y1  - 1989/03/01
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.35.3.372
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.35.3.372
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 372
EP  - 376
VL  - 35
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In this paper we apply the strategy of trend-damping to the popular Winters exponential smoothing systems for seasonal time series. Efficient model formulations are derived for both multiplicative and additive seasonal patterns. An algorithm is given to test the stability of the models in cases where predetermined smoothing parameters are used. Empirical results are presented to show that trend-damping improves ex ante forecast accuracy in seasonal data, especially at long leadtimes.
AB  - In this paper we apply the strategy of trend-damping to the popular Winters exponential smoothing systems for seasonal time series. Efficient model formulations are derived for both multiplicative and additive seasonal patterns. An algorithm is given to test the stability of the models in cases where predetermined smoothing parameters are used. Empirical results are presented to show that trend-damping improves ex ante forecast accuracy in seasonal data, especially at long leadtimes.
